Package: fastsave
Type: Package
Title: Serialization and compression of R objects using modern compressors
Version: 1.0
Date: 2020-04-18
Authors@R: c(
  person("Eduardo", "Gutierres", email = "eduardo.bull@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre", "cph")),
  person("Yann", "Collet", role = "cph", comment = "Bundled LZ4 code"),
  person("Google Inc.", role = "cph", comment = "Bundled Snappy code"),
  person("Facebook, Inc.", role = "cph", comment = "Bundled Zstandard code"))
Maintainer: Eduardo Gutierres <eduardo.bull@gmail.com>
Description: Serialization and compression of R objects using Zstandard, Snappy or LZ4 compressors,
  providing a faster alternative to saveRDS and readRDS.
License: MIT
Copyright: This package includes sources of the LZ4 library written
  by Yann Collet, of the Zstandard library owned by Facebook, Inc.
  and of the Snappy library owned by Google Inc.
LazyLoad: yes
Depends: R (>= 3.3.0)
LinkingTo: Rcpp
Imports: Rcpp
Suggests: 
  testthat,
  rbenchmark
RoxygenNote: 7.1.0
Encoding: UTF-8
NeedsCompilation: yes
SystemRequirements: C++11, cmake (>= 3.0.0)
